The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Tata Power profits steady

 OUR BUREAU

 May 30: Tata Power Co has announced a marginal increase in net profit at Rs 551.36 crore for 2004-05 compared with Rs 509.08 crore in the previous fiscal. 

 Revenues dipped to Rs 3,930.44 crore against Rs 4,239.08 crore in 2003-04. The decline is mainly due to a 10.1 per cent reduction in tariffs and higher fuel cost, the company said.

 The board has authorised the management to negotiate and finalise the sale of Tata Power Broadband to VSNL. 

 It has also decided on the sale of Tata Petrodyne for Rs 360 crore and the sale of Wadi Plant for a consideration of Rs 235.45 crore. 

 Adi Engineer, the former managing director of Tata Power, will oversee the management and operations of the company as Firdose Vandrevala, the present managing director, has stepped down.

 Colgate Palmolive earnings up

 Colgate Palmolive has reported a marginal rise in earnings for 2004-05 as it had to fork out Rs 6.40 crore towards a voluntary retirement scheme at the Aurangabad plant. The companys consolidated net profit rose to Rs 112.43 crore in 2004-05 compared with Rs 112.39 crore in the previous year. 

 The board had declared three interim dividends aggregating to 70 per cent (Rs 7 per share) for the fiscal, the company said in a release today.

 Total revenue during the year stood at Rs 999.39 crore against Rs 972.96 crore in the previous year, the release said.

 On a standalone basis, the company has posted a net profit of Rs 113.29 crore for the fiscal ended March 31 compared with Rs 108 crore in 2003-04. Revenues rose to Rs 998.45 crore (Rs 969.11 crore).

 In the fourth quarter ended March 31, the company has posted a net profit of Rs 32.34 crore (Rs 36.68 crore), while total revenue was stood at Rs 252.61 crore (Rs 236.84 crore).

 TVS Motor net dips

 Two-wheeler major TVS Motor Co today reported a marginal decline in net profit at Rs 137.57 crore for the fiscal ended March 31 compared with Rs 138.49 crore in the previous fiscal. Revenues rose 3 per cent at Rs 2,955.21 crore against Rs 2,856.42 crore in the previous year, said chairman and managing director Venu Srinivasan.




